@DATABASE "Top Gun"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - T - Top Gun"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - T
                   ====================================

                                  Top Gun
                                  =======



DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Infinite Lives" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(26460,0)"}          26460,0
@{"Lives = x     " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(27727,255) zxampoke(27728,255)"}        27727,x:27728,x (x= 1-255)


                         The "Infinite Lives" POKE is for a 1 player game.
                         The "Lives = x" POKE is for a 2 player game.

                         Change x to whatever value you wish, using
                         the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI. Simply
                         click the button to get the maximum value
                         x can be (usually 255).

                         I couldn't get this game to play properly,
                         so I don't know if the POKE works or not.

                         Rastan.
@endnode
